<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":1,"className":"has-gray-400-color has-text-color has-link-color","style":{"elements":{"link":{"color":{"text":"var:preset|color|grey-dark"}}},"typography":{"fontStyle":"normal","fontWeight":"400","textAlign":"left"}},"textColor":"grey-dark","fontSize":"heading-large"} -->
<h1 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-left has-gray-400-color has-text-color has-link-color has-grey-dark-color has-heading-large-font-size" style="font-style:normal;font-weight:400">Embassy of Cuba<br><em><em><em><mark style="background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)" class="has-inline-color has-primary-light-color">Document Legalization</mark></em></em></em></h1>
<!-- /wp:heading --></header>
<!-- /wp:group -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"fontSize":"medium"} -->
<p class="has-medium-font-size">Cuban embassy document legalization is essential when you need to have Canadian documents officially recognized in Cuba. Many of our clients need this service for marriage in Cuba, but legalization is also required for work, study, or other official matters in this beautiful country.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Documents destined for Cuba will need to be authenticated and legalized. But did you know that the documents will need to be translated to Spanish, and the translations will also need to be authenticated and legalized?</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"fontSize":"medium"} -->
<p class="has-medium-font-size">We specialize in navigating the Canadian legalization process for our clients. Whether you are gathering information or need immediate assistance, we can help! Phone us toll-free at <a href="tel:1-888-433-1011">1-888-433-1011</a>, or send us our quick Get Started form and we’ll get right back to you.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>
<!-- /wp:group -->

